  "title": "Nursing Aide [St. Andrew's Adult Home (Sengkang)]",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<p>· Conduct and record regular health check for residents</p>\n<p>· Assist in dispensing of medication, when necessary</p>\n<p>· Coordinate and escort clients for appointments at hospitals/ polyclinics</p>\n<p>· Provide personal hygiene, grooming care for the residents e.g. bathing, nail cutting etc where necessary</p>\n<p>· Support residents in maintaining/improving their daily living (ADLs), community living (CLSs) and Emotional &amp; Behavioral (EBMs) skills.</p>\n<p>· Coordinate with therapists/ psychologists and assist in the required interventions for residents</p>\n<p>· Facilitate and conduct activities programs e.g. art and craft, music &amp; dance, etc</p>\n<p>· Support residents for outings, events or interaction with volunteers/ donors.</p>\n<p>· Attend and submit reports of emergencies when it arises</p>\n<p>· Any other duties as may be assigned from time to time</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Specifications</strong></p>\n<p>·Must be a diploma / degree graduate in Nursing</p>\n<p>· Candidate with supervisory skills will be of advantage</p>\n<p>· PC literate and proficient in Microsoft Office applications</p>\n<p>· Able to work in a fast pace work environment</p>\n<p>· Have a sense of urgency and ability to prioritise</p>\n<p>· Experience in community/special needs settings will be advantageous.</p>",
